ie.cit.group3.domain

Class ChObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.cit.group3.domain.ChObject

  • @Entity
public class ChObject
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    John Murphy Student Id: R00131347 This class is used to store attributes of interest from the Cultural Heritage Objects JSON files. Jackson automatically extracts the data from the Json file for the attributes listed below. Each object can have just one: id, title, date, medium, creditline, description, gallery_text Each object may have several participations (captured in a List), and several Images (captured in a List of Maps. Map, where key is the image resolution and object is the images details). Updated to annotate this class for Entity/JPA Access.
